# Blog Post SEO Frontmatter

## Title (≤ 60 chars)

Google truncates at ~60–65 chars. Posts use `forceTitle` in `[slug].astro`, so no
`| SEWWA` suffix is appended — the raw title is what users see.

```yaml
title: "Schema Generator: JSON-LD Structured Data, Made Simple"
```

- ❌ Avoid parenthetical asides that push over 60: `"... (Would've Saved Me 100+ Hours)"`
- ✅ Front-load the primary keyword
- ✅ Include the year when the content is time-sensitive (`2026`)

## Description (140–158 chars)

Target 140–158 chars. Under 120 wastes space; over 158 gets truncated.

```yaml
description: "A 2026 guide to Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) — how to earn citations in AI answers and stay visible as AI search replaces traditional results."
```

- ✅ Include the primary keyword once, naturally
- ✅ End with a benefit or call-to-action clause
- ❌ No keyword stuffing, no clickbait

## Slug (no date prefix)

The folder name is `YYYY-MM-DD--slug/`, but the `slug` frontmatter field is the
**URL segment only**. Do not include the date prefix.

```yaml
# ✅ GOOD
slug: "google-ai-mode-seo-impact"

# ❌ BAD — produces /2026-04-12--google-ai-mode-seo-impact/
slug: "2026-04-12--google-ai-mode-seo-impact"
```

Rules: kebab-case, lowercase, no leading/trailing slashes, no date, no spaces.

## Image (optional, 1200×630 recommended)

- Omit `image` to use the site-wide `/og-image.png` default.
- If setting a per-post image, use 1200×630 (or same 1.905 aspect).
- Place in `public/og/` and reference as `/og/<slug>.png`.

## Tags (≥ 1, from allow-list)

Use exact names from `FRONTMATTER_TAGS` in `@constants`. First tag is used as
`articleSection` in JSON-LD, so pick the most specific one first.
